@NODE Requires "Requirements"

@{B}@{U}Requirements@{UB}@{UU}

Though PepperWatch is fully Plug'n Pray (tm)(c)(r) technology compatible,
it requires a 486DX or better computer system together
with winblows (c)(r)(tm) and 128MB of free RAM in 64KB blocks
as well as HIMEM.SYS, QEMM386.SYS, MEMMAKER.EXE, pNp compatible
BIOS, mother(f...er)board and so on installed properly and correctly
along with proper IRQ's, addresses etc...

Stop this sh.t!!!



You @{U}really@{UU} need only an Amiga (any model will do) with at least
OS2.04 to be able to run PepperWatch.

You may want to have also a SANA2 compatible network device installed
in DEVS:Networks/ and an appropriate protocol stack to be able to fully
enjoy the PepperWatch but it is not a prerequisite... :-)

Have fun!

@ENDNODE Requires





@NODE Install "Installation"

@{B}@{U}Installation@{UB}@{UU}

Since the current version can't be started from CLI,
it seems to me that the best place for PepperWatch is
the WBStartup drawer on Your SYS: partition.

Sorry for not supplying an Installer script for copying
or moving it there... :-)

Of course You may place it anywhere You want and start
it manually when needed.
@ENDNODE Install




