@ENDNODE Launch



@NODE Limits "Limitations"

@{B}@{U}Limitations in the current version:@{UB}@{UU}

	· not startable from CLI (actually it is startable but the args
	                          can be passed only via TOOLTYPES thus
	                          I advice You @{B}NOT@{UB} to try...)

	· no screennotify support yet

	· no security checks for invalid arguments except extreme DELAY values

	· no joystick support yet

@ENDNODE Limits




@NODE Bugs "Bugs"

@{B}@{U}Bugs in the current version:@{UB}@{UU}

	· I am sure there are some...

You may contact the @{"author" LINK Author} to report them!

@ENDNODE Bugs




@NODE Todos "TODOs"

@{B}@{U}TODOs in the current version:@{UB}@{UU}

	· screennotify support (now You have to quit PepperWatch when
	                        the WorkBench screen is to be closed)

	· support for public screens (other than WorkBench)

	· support for LOCALE (does anyone really need it?)

	· Polish version of the guide

	· more security checks for invalid arguments

	· CLI arguments parsing

	· Kempston joystick interface support :-)

	· better support (different image) for the "not configured" state

	· better support (animation?) for the "putting on/off" state

	· Online warning reminder (for saving phone bills)

	· line cost logger more accurate than CARRIER DETECT based ones

	· GLUE function for connecting PepperWatch's window with another one
	  may be useful when using along with a TM's dock for example like on
	  this @{"picture" system "MultiView >NIL: PepperWatch.iff5"}, where the rightmost gadget in the dock is the
	  PepperWatch's one.

	· some other ideas You may want to suggest


@ENDNODE Todos





@NODE History "Revision History"

@{B}@{U}Revision History@{UB}@{UU}

V0.91 (1996-12-10)	- 	First public release

V0.92 (1997-02-18)	-	Small optimisations. PepperWatch had been eating
						a few computrons (cpu cycles) more when the 
						monitored device was online. Corrected.

V0.93 (1997-02-19)	-	Added VERBOSE tooltype turning on the information
						for device, state, online time in the screentitle.
					-	Added icon for the guide.
					-	Small changes to the guide.

@ENDNODE History





